('khorailla1',	'Thank you so much for finding our missing people!'),
('khorailla2',	'It\'s not much, but I have some food if you\'d like.'),
('khorailla3',	'What ever will we do? Poor Ayell and Fayvara, I sure hope they\'re alright.'),
('khorailla4',	'You should talk to Maevalia over there.'),
('khorailla5',	'I\'m sorry, I\'m too distracted to help you right now.'),
('khorand',	'Hey you, don\'t even think of touching any of the crates. I am watching you!'),
('krell_1',	'Hey there. I am master Krell of the Knights of Elythom. How may we be of service?'),
('krell_2',	'Me and my band of knights are just visiting Remgard in .. shall we say .. unfinished business.'),
('krell_3',	'As to the nature of our business here, that is something I would rather not disclose.'),
('krell_4',	'We serve the order of Elythom.'),
('krell_jhaeld1',	'Shh, not so loud!'),
('krell_jhaeld10',	'For the sake of our order\'s reputation, please keep this to yourself if possible. We wouldn\'t want people to get the perception that the Knights of Elythom can be weakened in any way.'),
('krell_jhaeld2',	'Yes, we have heard the reports that people have gone missing here in Remgard. Most .. unfortunate.'),
('krell_jhaeld3',	'We even had one of our knights disappear on us. Now, due to the nature of our order, I presume you can see how that puts us in a .. peculiar situation.'),
('krell_jhaeld4',	'You see, usually it is us knights that find .. missing people. Now, we have had one of our own disappear. This has never happened before, and we are really unsure about what to do about it.'),
('krell_jhaeld5',	'Granted, people in our order have succumbed in combat to greater foes, but to just .. disappear without a trace, that\'s unheard of.'),
('krell_jhaeld6',	'We have a strong connection to each other, and to have someone leave the order would be unthinkable.'),
('krell_jhaeld7',	'As you can see, this puts us in a difficult situation.'),
('krell_jhaeld8',	'Well, we told the guards everything we know so far. They also seem to find this situation rather embarrassing, that they can\'t even keep a knight safe here in their town.'),
('krell_jhaeld9',	'We have no clues apart from the fact that she is missing, unfortunately. Where our sister knight is, is still a mystery to us.'),
('krell_knights_1',	'We are an order of knights that hail from Brimhaven.'),
('krell_knights_2',	'You should visit our compound in Brimhaven, if you ever make your way there.'),
('krell_knights_3',	'We serve all types of clients, from the wealthiest to even the poorest of poor.'),
('krell_knights_4',	'Regardless, we always get the job done.'),
('krell_knights_5',	'Mostly, we help people get back gold that other people owe them.'),
('krell_knights_6',	'We also help people find .. erm .. people that have gone missing.'),
('kuldan_1',	'Please report any suspicious behavior you might see.'),
('kuldan_2',	'I am Kuldan, captain of this here detachment of guards in Loneford. Now, if you will excuse me, I have work to do.'),
('kuldan_bc_1',	'What is this? This smells like Narwood poison. You say you retrieved this from Buceth?'),
('kuldan_bc_10',	'For the glory of Feygard, the people of Loneford may live on thanks to your help.'),
('kuldan_bc_2',	'But this means.. It is the water that the people are getting ill from? This explains a lot of things.'),
('kuldan_bc_3',	'You my friend have done Loneford a great service by finding this, and by extension, Feygard as well. We should go catch Buceth for what he has done.'),
('kuldan_bc_4',	'Dead you say? Hm, not quite the way we do things in Feygard, but I guess this is an exceptional case.'),
('kuldan_bc_5',	'I always suspected that those savages from Nor City were behind this all along.'),
('kuldan_bc_6',	'It\'s good to know that we now at least have some evidence to back up our claims.'),
('kuldan_bc_7',	'As for Loneford, I guess we will have to start bringing in water from Feygard to help the people here. Good thing they have us around, what would they do otherwise?'),
('kuldan_bc_8',	'And you, my friend - you should of course be sufficiently rewarded for your assistance in this matter. You should travel to the glorious city of Feygard to the northwest and report to the castle steward there for further instructions.'),
('kuldan_bc_9',	'I happen to know the castle steward personally, and I will send word to him about your help here.'),
('kuldan_c_1',	'Feygard is grateful for your assistance in solving the mystery of the illness here in Loneford.'),
('kuldan_c_2',	'We are trying to help the last few people that are still ill here now. Loneford might require our assistance from Feygard for quite some time.'),
('kuldan_guard',	'What? Talk to the boss.'),
('laecca_1',	'Hello. I am Laecca, mountain guide.'),
('laecca_10',	'Scratching their claws against the bare rock at night. *shrug*'),
('laecca_11',	'At first, I thought they were acting on pure instinct. But recently, I have started to believe they are smarter than regular beasts.'),
('laecca_12',	'Their attacks are getting more and more clever.'),
('laecca_13',	'You should talk to Guthbered. He is usually in the main hall. Look for a stone house in the center of the village.'),
('laecca_2',	'I keep an eye on the mountain pass, to make sure no more of those beasts make their way down here.'),
('laecca_3',	'Yeah, sure. It may sound that way. In reality, it\'s a lot of hard work.'),
('laecca_4',	'Very funny. I have to rest too you know. Keeping the monsters away is hard work.'),
('laecca_5',	'There used to be more of us mountain guides, but not many have survived the attack of the beasts.'),
('laecca_6',	'Perhaps.'),
('laecca_7',	'Anyway. I have some things to tend to. Nice talking to you.'),
('laecca_8',	'Thank you for your concern.'),
('laecca_9',	'Pfft, \'What beasts?\'. The Gornaud beasts of course.'),
('laede_1',	'You are welcome to rest here if you want. Pick any bed you wish.'),
('laede_2',	'I should warn you though that the one in the corner over there has a rotten stench to it. Someone must have spilled something onto it.'),
('laede_3',	'Welcome traveller. These beds are only for residents of Blackwater Mountain.'),
('landa_1',	'Wha? You!? No, get away from me!'),
('landa_10',	'It was in the middle of the night, on the day before everything started. The day after, I was sleeping it off during the day, so I didn\'t notice all the turmoil about when they brought Hesor back.'),
('landa_11',	'Almost the whole village wanted to see what had happened to Hesor. I kept to myself and didn\'t dare talk to anyone.'),
('landa_12',	'The same day, others started to get pale as well. I could see it in their faces.'),
('landa_13',	'The following night, I was getting ready to go to the well myself to look for any traces of what the boy had done.'),
('landa_14',	'I peeked out the window to see if there was anyone that might see me. Instead, I saw someone skulking around the well, filling up several vials with both dirt around the well, and water from the well itself.'),
('landa_15',	'I am sure it was Buceth, from the chapel. I have a good eye for people, and a good memory. Yes, I am sure it was Buceth.'),
('landa_16',	'Also, isn\'t it strange how Buceth has not gotten ill, while all the others in the village has gotten ill?'),
('landa_17',	'He must be up to something. He and that boy that looked like you. Are you sure it wasn\'t you?'),
('landa_18',	'Never mind. Please don\'t tell anyone that I told you all this.'),
('landa_19',	'Now, get out of here kid, before anyone sees you talking to me. *Looks around anxiously*'),
('landa_2',	'(Landa gives you a terrified look)'),
('landa_3',	'You were there! I ssssaw you!'),
('landa_4',	'Or was it you? No, it looked like you, and I have a good memory! *bites lip*'),
('landa_5',	'Get away from me, whatever you did over there, it\'s your business and I don\'t want any trouble!'),
('landa_6',	'Please don\'t hurt me!'),
('landa_7',	'No, you are smaller than him.'),
('landa_8',	'The boy. He was doing something. I tried to sneak up closer to see what it was he was doing, I did. But he ran away before I could see.'),
('landa_9',	'He did something by the well here in Loneford.'),
('landa_already_1',	'You again? I already told you. Get out of here before anyone sees you talking to me.'),
('larcal',	'I don\'t have time for you, kid. Get lost.'),
('larcal_1',	'Now now, what have we here? Are you implying that I have been down in Arcir\'s basement?'),
('larcal_2',	'So, maybe I was. The book is mine anyway.'),
('larcal_3',	'Look, let\'s solve this peacefully. You walk away and forget about that book, and you might still live.'),
('larcal_4',	'Good boy. Now run away.'),
('larcal_5',	'Ok, now you\'re starting to annoy me, kid. Get lost while you still can.'),
('larcal_6',	'You are still here? Ok then, if you want the book that bad, you will have to take it from me!'),
('larni_1',	'Hey, get out of here! This is my house!'),
('larni_2',	'(You see Larni holding his forehead.) Hey, *cough* get out of here! This is .. *cough* .. my house!'),
('larni_bed_1',	'You see a bed and nightstand.'),
('larni_bed_2',	'You see a bed and nightstand. The idol is still where you left it.'),
('larni_bed_3',	'You see a bed and nightstand. This must be Larni\'s bed.'),
('larni_bed_4',	'You hide the idol under the bed.'),
('lbridge',	'You will not pass me.'),
('leonid1',	'Hello kid. You\'re Mikhail\'s son aren\'t you? With that brother of yours.\n\nI\'m Leonid, steward of Crossglen village.'),
('leonid_andor',	'Your brother? No, I haven\'t seen him here today. I think I saw him in here yesterday talking to Gruil. Maybe he knows more?'),
('leonid_bye',	'Shadow be with you.'),
('leonid_continue',	'Anything else I can help you with?'),
('leonid_crossglen',	'As you know, this is Crossglen village. Mostly a farming community.'),
('leonid_crossglen1',	'We have Audir with his smithy to the southwest, Leta and her husband\'s cabin to the west, this town hall here and your father\'s cabin to the northwest.'),
('leonid_crossglen2',	'That\'s pretty much it. We try to live a peaceful life.'),
('leonid_crossglen3',	'There were some recent disturbances some weeks ago that you may have noticed. Some villagers got into a fight over the new decree from Lord Geomyr.'),
('leonid_crossglen4',	'Lord Geomyr issued a statement regarding the unlawful use of Bonemeal as healing substance. Some villagers argued that we should oppose Lord Geomyr\'s word and still use it.'),
('leonid_crossglen4_1',	'Tharal, our priest, was particularly upset and suggested we do something about Lord Geomyr.'),
('leonid_crossglen5',	'Other villagers argued that we should follow Lord Geomyr\'s decree.\n\nPersonally, I haven\'t decided what my thoughts are.'),
('leonid_crossglen6',	'On one hand, Lord Geomyr supports Crossglen with a lot of protection. *points to the soldiers in the hall*'),
('leonid_crossglen7',	'But on the other hand, the tax and the recent changes of what\'s allowed are really taking a toll on Crossglen.'),
('leonid_crossglen8',	'Someone should go to Castle Geomyr and talk to the steward about our situation here in Crossglen.'),
('leonid_crossglen9',	'In the meantime, we\'ve banned all use of Bonemeal as a healing substance.'),
('leta1',	'Hey, this is my house, get out of here!'),
('leta2',	'Beat it kid, get out of my house!'),
('leta_oromir1',	'Do you know anything about my husband? He should be here helping me with the farm today, but he seems to be missing as usual.\nSigh.'),
('leta_oromir2',	'If you see him, tell him to hurry back here and help me with the housework.\nNow get out of here!'),
('leta_oromir_complete',	'Hiding is he? That\'s not surprising. I\'ll go let him know who\'s the boss around here.\nThanks for letting me know though.'),
('leta_oromir_complete2',	'Thanks for telling me about Oromir earlier. I will go get him in just a minute.'),
('lethenlor0',	'Can I help you?'),
('lethenlor1',	'Well, it\'s our cabin. What are you doing here, anyway?'),
('lethenlor2',	'Hrmpf. I think you had better leave.'),
('lethenlor3',	'Ok. Good luck with that.'),
('lethenlor4',	'Does it matter? I don\'t know you, and you don\'t know me.'),
('lethenlor5',	'He he. Interesting. Let\'s just say our line of work is .. interesting.'),
('lethenlor6',	'But never mind that. I heard there were some troubles up by the Charwood mining town recently.'),
('lethenlor7',	'It\'s just northeast of here. Look for the Charwood cabin north of here.'),
('lleglaris0',	'Are you sure you should be here? Maybe you should go play with .. your toys or something?'),
('lleglaris1',	'Ha ha. I can be as rude as I want!'),
('lleglaris10',	'Undead things. Yuck, that smell.'),
('lleglaris11',	'I saw this hole in the ground that they seemed to come out of. The ground had been completely corrupted around it.'),
('lleglaris12',	'Anyway, I ran away and my amulet must have gotten stuck on a branch or something like that.'),
('lleglaris13',	'Yeah, that\'s what I though as well.'),
('lleglaris14',	'Good.'),
('lleglaris15',	'Go look just east of my cabin here. You probably need to take the path north when you exit the cabin, and then head east.'),
('lleglaris2',	'Hah! Please enlighten me.'),
('lleglaris3',	'That was you? Hah! And you expect me to believe that?'),
('lleglaris4',	'Good for you. It looks just like any other trinket to me.'),
('lleglaris5',	'Ha ha! Now, that\'s funny!'),
('lleglaris6',	'You have my best wishes, kid. Hope you\'ll get to see the world some day.'),
('lleglaris7',	'If you\'re such an experienced adventurer, I\'m sure a small task of mine wouldn\'t be any problem for you?'),
('lleglaris8',	'I\'ve lost an amulet of mine. I was out in the woods around the cabin here and heard a noise coming from the east.'),
('lleglaris9',	'Tired as I was, I didn\'t notice the things coming out from behind the trees fast enough.'),
('lleglaris_r1',	'Hi again. Did you find my amulet?'),
('lleglaris_r2',	'Ok then. I won\'t keep you.'),
('lleglaris_r3',	'Yes, that\'s the one. It\'s good to see it back in my hands again.'),
('lleglaris_r4',	'Thank you for finding my amulet.'),
('lleglaris_r5',	'Maybe you really are an experienced adventurer after all.'),
('lleglaris_r6',	'Anyway, see this table here? It\'s just some old trinkets that I\'ve gathered along the years. Maybe some of them could come in handy for you?'),
('lleglaris_rej',	'With you? No way. You look way to inexperienced.'),
('lodar0_g0',	'Teehee. You funny looking.'),
('lodar0_g0a',	'You again?'),
('lodar0_g1',	'He he, but funny not enough to let you pass.'),
('lodar0_g2',	'Master says only ones with password can pass. You have password?'),
('lodar0_g3',	'You know! You know!'),
('lodar0_g4',	'[The creature moves out of the way, and gestures with its hands almost like it is welcoming you further into the forest]'),
('lodar0_gfail',	'You not know password! Teehee.'),
('lodar0_gfail1',	'[The guardian pushes you away and shakes its head]'),
('lodar13_rest',	'You are not allowed to use Aulowenn\'s bed.'),
('lodar_0',	'Maybe under here? No.'),
('lodar_1',	'Maybe over there .. Yikes! Who are you!?'),
('lodar_10',	'Maybe it was in here ..'),
('lodar_11',	'No.. Hm, wait. You! Maybe you can be of use here, if you are willing to help?'),
('lodar_12',	'Good. Take this stone, it will allow you to enter the tomb. Go below. Return once you\'re done.\n\n[Lodar hands you an odd looking stone that seems to be glowing from within]'),
('lodar_13b',	'Good. Now, hurry, before the Hira\'zinn moves again!'),
('lodar_14',	'I thought I make it very clear before. With the stone in your possession, you will be able to enter the tomb. Go below. Return once you\'re done.'),
('lodar_2',	'Well, it doesn\'t matter who you are anyway. I am Lodar, maker of potions.'),
('lodar_2a',	'Don\'t know. What difference does it make? I must get all this done before the Hira\'zinn moves.'),
('lodar_3',	'Yes yes, the Hira\'zinn. As I said, I must find the correct mixture before it moves again.'),
('lodar_4',	'Now, where were they? Over here perhaps?'),
('lodar_5',	'No, maybe I should add some of the ..'),
('lodar_6a',	'Oh yes. Can you please move a bit, you are in the way. Can\'t you see I\'m busy with finding a way to stop the spread of the Hira\'zinn here?'),
('lodar_6b',	'Didn\'t I tell you? I must find the correct mixture before the Hira\'zinn spreads further.'),
('lodar_7',	'Everything was fine up until a few days ago. That\'s when everything started to happen.'),
('lodar_8',	'It never used to be like this, or did it? I can\'t remember.'),
('lodar_9',	'Doesn\'t matter. I must make it stop anyway.'),
('lodar_andor0',	'Oh, you must be referring to that other boy that was here recently.'),
('lodar_andor1',	'He did not tell me his name, but he had some similarities to how you look. Yes, then he probably was the person you are looking for.'),
('lodar_andor10',	'So, he asked for a sample of Narwood extract. Normally, I wouldn\'t give that out to just anyone.'),
('lodar_andor11',	'However, as I said, there was something odd about this whole meeting. I actually felt a bit threatened, even though he was so polite and friendly.'),
('lodar_andor12',	'Fearing something would happen to me if I rejected his request, I reluctantly gave him a small sample of the Narwood extract.'),
('lodar_andor13',	'He gladly accepted the sample, and left shortly after. That\'s when it started to get even more odd.'),
('lodar_andor14',	'As he left, I happened to glance out the window. There, in the forest I saw the bright flash of the light from the sun hitting a blade.'),
('lodar_andor15',	'If I hadn\'t seen that light coming off the blade, I would not have spotted the person there at all. He seemed to be hiding in the forest.'),
('lodar_andor16',	'Yes, so it would seem. It was quite obvious that he did not want me to spot him. After your brother left, I saw them both speak some words to each other, before they both left together.'),
('lodar_andor17',	'Yes, that\'s basically it. But that\'s not all.'),
('lodar_andor18',	'Shortly after they left, strange things started happening in the forest.'),
('lodar_andor19',	'I saw a pack of wolves that were fighting each other. Tearing up each others sides, and eating the remains.'),
('lodar_andor2',	'You say his name is Andor? That\'s an odd name, don\'t you think?'),
('lodar_andor20',	'I saw birds flying over my cabin, totally covered in red blood. Blood covered birds - now that\'s something that I have not even heard about.'),
('lodar_andor21',	'I tell you, something affected the forest. Myself, I felt my stomach turning even more often that it usually does.'),
('lodar_andor22',	'I had this strong urge to eat more than usual. I even found myself having lapses of time where I could not remember what I had done for the past couple of hours.'),
('lodar_andor23',	'In hindsight, I think it\'s pretty clear what started to happen. The Hira\'zinn awoke. To make matters worse, at least for me, it awoke in the tomb beneath my cabin here.'),
('lodar_andor24',	'What I find disturbing is that this all started to happen right after your brother and that other person were here.'),
('lodar_andor25',	'Maybe they visited that tomb. Now, I\'m not pointing any fingers here, but it certainly seems like they had something to do with this, considering that the tomb has been quiet for ages.'),
('lodar_andor25a',	'I don\'t know the details of course, and I have no proof. I only know that asking for Narwood extract is an odd request, and that the Hira\'zinn started to creep up on me shortly after that.'),
('lodar_andor26',	'Now, I am no expert in these things. I have only read bits and pieces from old books. I mostly focus my thoughts on herbs, mixtures and potions.'),
('lodar_andor27',	'But I do know other people that might be able to provide you with further guidance.'),
('lodar_andor28',	'Since you defeated the Hira\'zinn, I think those people would be more than happy to speak to you. I would be happy to help you in any way I can too, of course.'),
('lodar_andor29',	'Seek out Lady Lydalon in the Valanyr temple of the Shadow in Nor City. She is one of the wisest people I know, and an excellent mentor.'),
('lodar_andor3',	'Anyway, enough of that. What would you like to know?'),
('lodar_andor30',	'Here, take this letter.'),
('lodar_andor31',	'Present the letter to the guards at the temple, and they will grant you an audience with Lady Lydalon.'),
('lodar_andor32',	'Also, while you\'re there, please give her my warmest regards. It has been too long since I last visited her.'),
('lodar_andor32a',	'Show some respect will you?'),
('lodar_andor33',	'Just one more thing.'),
('lodar_andor34',	'The person that was hiding among the trees here, that your brother was travelling with - I happened to get a quick view of his cloak.'),
('lodar_andor35',	'I\'ve seen cloaks like that before. The fabric is similar to a fabric commonly used in Nor City.'),
('lodar_andor36',	'It could mean that whatever group of people he belongs to - there might be more of them in Nor City. Either you might want to stay away from them, or seek them out. You decide.'),
('lodar_andor37',	'You have done a great deed here. Goodbye. Take care, my friend.'),
('lodar_andor4',	'Well, even from the first time I saw him, I knew something odd was going on.'),
('lodar_andor5',	'He seemed overly friendly to me, almost like he seemed to know me already.'),
('lodar_andor6',	'You should know that most people that stumble into my cabin here have either been lost in the maze some time, or are just happy to see another living being.'),
('lodar_andor7',	'He showed no such signs. Almost like he knew who I was and that he expected me to be here.'),
('lodar_andor8',	'He very kindly asked for some Narwood extract.'),
('lodar_andor9',	'It can be used to make quite a nasty poison.'),
('lodar_andor9a',	'Those poor poor people. They have my sympathies. I hope it\'s not my things that brought this misery upon them.'),
('lodar_d0',	'Hello again.'),
('lodar_d1',	'Again, thank you for your help.'),
('lodar_fg1_1',	'You there! What are you doing here?'),
('lodar_fg1_10',	'Another guard said he\'d nearly gotten lost in a what he called the \'green maze\'.'),
('lodar_fg1_11',	'Yes, it seems so. None of the scouts have come back. Or rather, the ones that have come back have been .. afflicted by something.'),
('lodar_fg1_12',	'I don\'t know. Maybe something in the woods.'),
('lodar_fg1_13',	'Maybe it\'s something that the madman that we were looking for has done.'),
('lodar_fg1_14',	'No, none.'),
('lodar_fg1_15',	'Oh, before you go. As I told you before, one of the guards mentioned \'the green maze\', that apparently is somewhere around here.'),
('lodar_fg1_16',	'Thank you.'),
('lodar_fg1_17',	'I don\'t know if it\'s the twisty paths themselves or something that the madman has done that caused my fellow guards to behave the way they have - but consider yourself warned if you venture further into the forest!'),
('lodar_fg1_18',	'Consider yourself warned. I can\'t come help you if something happens.'),
('lodar_fg1_2',	'This place is not safe. I urge you to turn back and to venture no further into this cursed forest.'),
('lodar_fg1_3',	'This place - oh why did we ever agree to go on this mission?'),
('lodar_fg1_4',	'Me and some other guards were sent here to find a madman that is wanted by the Feygard authorities.'),
('lodar_fg1_5',	'The madman is wanted for a number of crimes committed against Feygard, none of which I am allowed to disclose.'),
('lodar_fg1_6',	'At first, it seemed like just any ordinary mission - go find some crazy fool.'),
('lodar_fg1_7',	'But once we got here, it started happening. One by one, my fellow guards got more and more .. well .. I don\'t know how to put it, but something started to happen to them.'),
('lodar_fg1_8',	'The first guard said he had seen something among the trees, and went to look for it. We never saw him again.'),
('lodar_fg1_8a',	'Now, these flies that inhabit these woods can drive a grown man mad, I\'ll tell you that. But that wasn\'t it. There was something else.'),
('lodar_fg1_9',	'Some time later, one of the other guards seemed like he didn\'t know who we were, and ran off into the forest.'),
('lodar_fg1_r1',	'Oh, it\'s you again.'),
('lodar_fg1_r2',	'Oh, it\'s you again.'),
('lodar_fg2_0',	'What? Who are you?'),
('lodar_fg2_1',	'No no. You are too small. You can\'t be him.'),
('lodar_fg2_2',	'Crazy old fool, that\'s what they said he\'d be.'),
('lodar_fg2_3',	'Ha ha. Crazy!'),
('lodar_fg2_4',	'(the guard mumbles something that you can\'t understand)'),
('lodar_fg2_5',	'Must get away! Soon we all will be able to see it.'),
('lodar_fg2_6',	'(the guard continues with his mumbling)'),
('lodar_fg2_a',	'Ouch, my head. It hurts so much.'),
('lodar_fg3_0',	'(the guard stares back at you without saying anything)'),
('lodar_fg3_1',	'(you notice him breathing heavily, and that his hands are shaking furiously)'),
